HEADWORD: Sugary
<hw>Sug"ar*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Resembling or containing sugar; tasting of sugar; sweet.</def>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fond of sugar or sweet things; <as>as, a
<ex>sugary</ex> palate</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sugescent</ent>⟦br⟧
